have you ever written a personal spontaneous and emotional love letter i mean something that comes directly from your heart not pre rehearsed or coached i will miss this class great people but you most of all you brightened each and every day i spent there the charm of your glow and the easy manner of your gentleness captured me from the start something like that and i received an answer which i still have received your letter and was quite shocked to put it mildly this happened many years ago when times were different than now we used stamps and paper to express our inner feelings please comment with your own input and let me be the judge thank you ms scarlet i asked this question because i carry u s mail for a living personal letters are going the way of the dinosaur it's me you passed me right by with points hey len i have written so many letters from the heart to friends family loves and especially to my son i miss the personal aspect of the written letter where have you been anyway Social rule Past teachings of Prem Rawat Sydney Riot of 1879 Royal Assent Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Cliff Richard Photography One Tree Hill (TV series) God Emperor of Dune Sharon Tate The Beatles Harry Potter and the Order of the Phoenix Current teachings of Prem Rawat Mail Asperger syndrome Kurt Cobain Kill Bill Sexual orientation A Course In Miracles United States Postal Service Hey Jude Shaggy dog story Appeal F. Scott Fitzgerald Ludwig Wittgenstein The Amber Spyglass Negima Big Brother UK series 6 The Descent of Man, and Selection in Relation to Sex Postage stamp Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind Chuck Palahniuk Futurama (TV series - season 5) Rent (musical) Theory of conduct Abortion Whose Line Is It Anyway? Empathy She Loves You Billboard Hot 100 Friedrich Schleiermacher The Curse of Fenric Internet troll Miss Saigon Arjuna Warren G. Harding The Lovely Bones False memory Priesthood (Mormonism) Wheel of Fortune Emotions (album) Mojave people Time Out of Mind E